WEBVTT

00:02.087 --> 00:04.046
[eerie music]

00:04.130 --> 00:05.882
♪♪

01:35.054 --> 01:37.223
[birds chirping]

02:19.849 --> 02:21.643
[radio playing]

02:21.726 --> 02:23.478
♪♪

02:50.338 --> 02:51.798
How was everything?

02:51.881 --> 02:54.175
Real good, honey. Thanks.

02:54.259 --> 02:56.594
Let me have a pack of
Kools, too, will you?

02:56.678 --> 02:58.179
[radio]
<i>♪ We'll just keep on rolling</i>

02:58.263 --> 03:01.015
<i>♪ 'Till we don't know
where we are</i>

03:03.184 --> 03:04.727
<i>♪ You know, I've had enough</i>

03:04.811 --> 03:08.731
<i>♪ Of this same 'ol
song and dance</i>

03:09.983 --> 03:12.569
<i>♪ And nothing going to change...</i>

03:12.652 --> 03:14.279
Real nice smile
you got there.

03:14.362 --> 03:15.530
Thank you.

03:16.114 --> 03:16.865
Goodbye.

03:16.906 --> 03:18.157
Bye.

03:41.347 --> 03:42.181
<i>[gun shot]</i>

03:42.265 --> 03:43.266
<i>[screaming]</i>

03:43.349 --> 03:44.100
<i>Shut up!</i>

03:44.142 --> 03:46.519
<i>[gun shots]</i>

03:50.523 --> 03:53.359
<i>[siren wailing]</i>

03:57.322 --> 03:58.907
[car radio playing]

03:58.990 --> 04:00.700
♪♪

04:03.453 --> 04:06.539
<i>♪ Look here girl,
better listen to me</i>

04:07.665 --> 04:11.878
<i>♪ What we got here
is a love can't be denied</i>

04:11.961 --> 04:14.213
<i>♪ I told your mama
and your daddy, too</i>

04:14.297 --> 04:16.423
<i>♪ Don't you look back girl,
I'm warning you</i>

04:16.507 --> 04:18.216
<i>♪ Hear me now,
I'm telling you--</i>

04:20.470 --> 04:22.639
[eerie music]

04:22.722 --> 04:24.641
♪♪

04:27.352 --> 04:30.355
[telephone ringing]

04:31.648 --> 04:34.484
[voices echoing]
<i>Ooh, baby...</i>

04:43.034 --> 04:45.495
<i>Ooh, baby...</i>

04:45.578 --> 04:47.121
<i>Shut up!</i>

04:47.956 --> 04:49.165
<i>[glass breaking]</i>

04:49.248 --> 04:51.125
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

04:51.209 --> 04:53.044
<i>Die, bitch!</i>

04:53.127 --> 04:53.920
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

04:53.962 --> 04:55.630
<i>Die!</i>

04:58.383 --> 05:00.551
[car radio playing]
<i>♪ Well, I don't need
a big fancy car</i>

05:00.635 --> 05:02.762
<i>♪ Whatever I can drive
to get near the store</i>

05:02.845 --> 05:06.808
<i>♪ I just want to be
where you are, Lalana</i>

05:06.891 --> 05:08.768
<i>♪ Lalana</i>

05:09.644 --> 05:11.062
<i>♪ Ah... Oh...</i>

05:11.145 --> 05:12.397
[news announcer]
<i> Weather in the
Chicagoland area,</i>

05:12.480 --> 05:14.232
<i>fifty percent chance of rain
tonight and tomorrow,</i>

05:14.315 --> 05:15.650
<i>but maybe we'll get
lucky again</i>

05:15.733 --> 05:17.151
<i>and see some sunshine
for the weekend.</i>

05:17.235 --> 05:19.862
<i>Highs around the 60s
and, uh, oh, we might be</i>

05:19.946 --> 05:21.864
<i>getting down to the old
freezing point by tonight.</i>

05:21.990 --> 05:24.158
[birds chirping]
[water trickling]

05:30.540 --> 05:32.417
<i>[fabric tearing]</i>

05:32.500 --> 05:34.961
<i>[woman's muffled screaming]</i>

05:37.046 --> 05:39.215
<i>[water splashing]</i>

06:14.083 --> 06:16.669
Well, Kathy's mom
said she could do it.

06:20.256 --> 06:22.216
[car engine starting]

06:33.061 --> 06:35.021
[car engine starting]

06:53.456 --> 06:55.208
[eerie music]

06:55.291 --> 06:57.251
♪♪

08:37.226 --> 08:38.895
Hi, are you
going to the city?

08:38.977 --> 08:40.770
Sure. Hop in.

09:05.254 --> 09:08.174
[PA announcement]
<i> Southwest Airlines paging
Linda Connell.</i>

09:08.674 --> 09:11.469
<i>Linda Connell, please come to
the Southwest ticket counter.</i>

09:17.767 --> 09:19.143
Becky?

09:20.019 --> 09:21.812
Hello, Otis.

09:25.816 --> 09:27.652
Well, how are you?

09:27.735 --> 09:28.903
Good.

09:28.986 --> 09:29.820
It's good to see you.

09:29.904 --> 09:31.656
Good to see you, too.

09:31.739 --> 09:33.574
You got all your things?

09:33.658 --> 09:34.867
Yeah.

09:37.912 --> 09:40.164
You look terrible.

09:43.918 --> 09:44.669
[crying]

09:44.710 --> 09:46.671
Okay, come on.
Let's go.

09:46.754 --> 09:48.547
It's this way.

10:01.519 --> 10:02.853
Before you got
married I told you

10:02.937 --> 10:04.689
Leroy was no damn good.

10:04.772 --> 10:06.524
That he was trash
and he'd always be trash

10:06.607 --> 10:08.401
and you was going to catch it
and you did, didn't you?

10:08.484 --> 10:10.027
I don't really want to
talk about him right now.

10:10.111 --> 10:12.113
Okay by me, we don't
have to talk about it now.

10:12.196 --> 10:13.906
We don't have to
talk about it ever.

10:13.990 --> 10:16.075
How long are you
going to be up here?

10:16.158 --> 10:17.201
It's hard to say.

10:17.285 --> 10:18.160
What about Lurleen?

10:18.244 --> 10:19.662
How long can you
leave her with Mama?

10:19.745 --> 10:20.955
I don't know.

10:21.038 --> 10:23.165
I'm going to get a job,
make some money.

10:23.249 --> 10:25.459
Maybe bring her up here,
I don't know.

10:25.543 --> 10:26.669
Where did you tell Leroy
you were going?

10:26.752 --> 10:28.045
I don't want
to talk about him.

10:28.129 --> 10:30.923
Okay, we don't have
to talk about him!

10:33.592 --> 10:34.969
You hungry?

10:35.052 --> 10:36.053
Yeah.

10:36.137 --> 10:37.930
Good, I'm hungry, too.

10:39.098 --> 10:41.225
You think Leroy's hungry?

10:41.976 --> 10:43.561
[chuckles]

10:44.770 --> 10:46.647
Do you want some more coffee?

10:46.731 --> 10:47.815
Yeah, thanks.

10:47.898 --> 10:49.275
Here.

11:00.202 --> 11:02.121
So what kind of work do you
planning on getting up here?

11:02.204 --> 11:03.331
Anything like...

11:03.414 --> 11:05.041
I haven't decided yet.

11:05.124 --> 11:07.168
What else can you do
besides dance naked?

11:07.251 --> 11:08.711
Don't start with me, Otis.

11:08.794 --> 11:10.755
I can do lots of things,
mister.

11:10.838 --> 11:11.922
Oh yeah? Like what?

11:12.006 --> 11:13.382
Like waitressing

11:13.466 --> 11:14.592
or a beautician.

11:14.675 --> 11:15.760
Yeah.

11:15.843 --> 11:18.804
After seeing you I might
just try brain surgery.

11:18.888 --> 11:20.973
[chuckles]

11:21.057 --> 11:22.808
You're a card.

11:22.892 --> 11:24.143
Yeah, I'm the queen.

11:24.226 --> 11:26.187
Yeah, the queen of clubs.

11:28.314 --> 11:30.608
[laughing]

11:30.691 --> 11:33.486
Don't make me sorry
I came here, Otis.

11:35.363 --> 11:37.323
[door opening]

11:42.411 --> 11:43.204
Howdy.

11:43.287 --> 11:44.497
Hey, Henry.

11:44.580 --> 11:46.207
I brought you a present.

11:47.333 --> 11:49.460
Where did you get that?

11:49.543 --> 11:50.961
Picked it up.

11:53.923 --> 11:55.049
Whew!

11:55.132 --> 11:55.925
Pretty nice, huh?

11:56.008 --> 11:58.010
Sure is a beauty.

12:00.763 --> 12:02.723
[playing guitar]

12:09.605 --> 12:10.856
Oh, uh...

12:10.940 --> 12:13.526
Henry, this here
is my sister, Becky.

12:13.609 --> 12:15.653
She's gonna be staying here
with us for a while,

12:15.736 --> 12:16.862
like I said.

12:16.946 --> 12:18.948
Becky, this here's Henry.

12:19.031 --> 12:20.533
Hello, Henry.

12:20.616 --> 12:21.450
Hello, Becky.

12:21.534 --> 12:23.452
Good to meet you.

12:23.536 --> 12:25.788
She don't look
nothing like you,

12:25.871 --> 12:26.831
that's for sure.

12:26.914 --> 12:28.457
Lucky for her.

12:29.125 --> 12:30.793
Henry's on his way out west.

12:30.876 --> 12:31.710
Oh, where?

12:31.794 --> 12:32.920
California.

12:33.003 --> 12:34.797
Oh.

12:34.880 --> 12:36.424
She can sleep
on the couch.

12:36.507 --> 12:38.092
No, no.

12:38.175 --> 12:40.678
Listen, Becky, I want you
to take the spare room.

12:40.761 --> 12:42.263
No, Henry,
thank you but no...

12:42.346 --> 12:43.889
I insist.

12:43.973 --> 12:45.391
Ain't that right, Otis?

12:45.474 --> 12:46.684
Up to you.

12:47.643 --> 12:48.978
Alright,

12:49.061 --> 12:51.272
but if it gets to be
a bother, we'll change.

12:51.355 --> 12:52.606
Fair enough.

12:52.690 --> 12:53.607
Well, I got to get going.

12:53.691 --> 12:55.192
I got some work to do today.

12:55.276 --> 12:56.902
<i>I just stopped by
to clean up a little.</i>

12:56.986 --> 12:57.862
Where you working?

12:57.945 --> 13:01.115
<i>I'm helping Andy spray
some houses off La Grange.</i>

13:01.198 --> 13:03.200
Oh, so that's working
out for you, huh?

13:03.284 --> 13:04.493
<i>Yeah.</i>

13:04.577 --> 13:06.162
Sounds like fun.

13:06.954 --> 13:07.872
Coffee?

13:07.955 --> 13:10.541
No thanks, I gotta go.

13:13.461 --> 13:14.837
See ya.

13:14.920 --> 13:16.505
Yeah.

13:40.488 --> 13:41.989
<i>That's it till next week.</i>

13:42.072 --> 13:44.033
<i>I was hoping for
a little more work.</i>

13:44.116 --> 13:45.910
<i>So was I.</i>

13:48.996 --> 13:50.331
You never know.

13:50.414 --> 13:51.790
Sometimes I get a call.

13:51.874 --> 13:53.000
You know,

13:53.083 --> 13:57.379
these assholes want you to
be out there the next day.

13:57.463 --> 13:58.297
You never know.

13:58.380 --> 13:59.632
Yeah.

13:59.715 --> 14:02.593
Here, take this.

14:02.676 --> 14:04.470
We'll call it a retainer.

14:04.553 --> 14:05.346
Thanks.

14:05.387 --> 14:06.931
You don't here from me

14:07.014 --> 14:08.807
give me a call.

14:09.517 --> 14:11.727
Hold on.
Don't forget your sprayer.

14:11.810 --> 14:13.437
Hang onto it.

14:15.564 --> 14:16.774
Okay.

14:20.194 --> 14:21.946
Come on, kid,
come on.

14:22.029 --> 14:23.656
Throw it in there.

14:23.739 --> 14:24.782
Good catch.

14:26.075 --> 14:27.868
Put a spiral on it.

14:28.702 --> 14:30.079
Nice catch.

14:32.831 --> 14:34.416
Sorry about that.

14:34.750 --> 14:36.627
[eerie music]

14:36.710 --> 14:38.254
♪♪

15:18.794 --> 15:20.588
[cartoon]
<i>- Calling all cars,
calling all cars.</i>

15:20.671 --> 15:22.923
<i>Calling all cars,
calling all cars.</i>

15:44.528 --> 15:45.571
<i>[crash]</i>

15:45.654 --> 15:47.656
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

15:49.533 --> 15:52.119
<i>[sounds of a struggle]</i>

16:23.609 --> 16:24.985
It's good.

16:29.698 --> 16:32.701
And please check
the left rear tire.

16:42.795 --> 16:44.713
It's good, too.

16:44.797 --> 16:46.674
Thank you.

16:46.757 --> 16:48.133
Yeah.

16:56.266 --> 16:58.435
And what can
I do for you, sir?

16:58.519 --> 17:00.813
You got any more of
what you had last week?

17:00.896 --> 17:02.064
I might.

17:02.147 --> 17:04.023
Well, do you
or don't you?

17:04.108 --> 17:05.608
Yeah.

17:05.693 --> 17:06.652
Well?

17:06.734 --> 17:09.195
Well, I don't have
it on me, stupid.

17:10.071 --> 17:11.656
Give me the money.

17:16.744 --> 17:17.871
I'll bring it
around the field.

17:17.954 --> 17:19.415
I don't want you
hanging around practice.

17:19.498 --> 17:20.915
Give me my money back.

17:20.999 --> 17:22.209
Up to you.

17:24.545 --> 17:26.755
Be in the parking lot
at 6:30.

17:28.716 --> 17:29.842
Sure thing.

17:29.925 --> 17:31.427
6:30 tomorrow.

17:31.510 --> 17:32.344
Tomorrow?

17:32.428 --> 17:34.096
Take it or leave it.

17:34.179 --> 17:35.055
Great.

17:35.139 --> 17:36.557
See ya.

17:40.811 --> 17:42.479
Fuckin' pervert.

17:42.646 --> 17:44.440
[car engine starting]

17:52.489 --> 17:55.159
Ugh, this is so gross.

17:55.242 --> 17:57.619
I always did hate doing this.

17:57.703 --> 17:58.662
I'll do it.

17:58.746 --> 18:00.372
That's alright.

18:01.373 --> 18:03.876
[plucking guitar string]

18:05.419 --> 18:07.129
Where did you say
you met him?

18:07.212 --> 18:08.547
Who?

18:08.839 --> 18:11.341
You know who. Henry.

18:11.425 --> 18:14.011
What do you want
to know for?

18:14.094 --> 18:15.262
I don't know.

18:15.345 --> 18:17.139
I'm just curious.

18:18.932 --> 18:20.392
Vandalia.

18:21.101 --> 18:22.519
Vandalia?

18:22.603 --> 18:24.730
Sure, Vandalia.

18:24.813 --> 18:26.148
Oh.

18:26.231 --> 18:28.108
What was he in for?

18:28.192 --> 18:30.110
You don't want to know.

18:30.194 --> 18:32.029
What did he do,
kill his mama?

18:32.112 --> 18:33.155
Uh-huh.

18:33.238 --> 18:35.282
Come on,
what was he in for?

18:35.365 --> 18:36.241
You don't want to know.

18:36.325 --> 18:38.869
What did he do,
rob a bank or something?

18:38.952 --> 18:41.497
You were right the first time.

18:41.580 --> 18:44.500
- Huh?
- You were right
the first time.

18:44.583 --> 18:47.085
He killed his mama.

18:47.169 --> 18:49.379
Don't you ever
tell him I told you.

18:49.463 --> 18:50.422
You're kidding me?

18:50.506 --> 18:52.216
- No, I ain't.
- Yes, you are.

18:52.299 --> 18:53.759
Alright, I'm kidding you.

18:53.842 --> 18:56.136
Just don't ever
tell him I told you.

18:56.220 --> 18:58.013
He killed his mama?

18:58.096 --> 18:59.556
With a baseball bat.

18:59.640 --> 19:01.934
Her and one of her
boyfriends.

19:02.017 --> 19:03.519
I swear, if you ever
tell him I told you

19:03.602 --> 19:05.145
I'll beat your ass right off.

19:05.229 --> 19:06.396
How do you know all this?

19:06.480 --> 19:08.106
He told me,
that's how I know.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.233
How else would I know?

19:09.316 --> 19:10.400
Were you cellmates
or something?

19:10.484 --> 19:13.320
No, we were friends.

19:13.403 --> 19:14.613
When did he get out?

19:14.696 --> 19:16.615
A couple of years before me.

19:18.992 --> 19:20.786
[door opening]

19:25.082 --> 19:26.416
Hi.

19:26.500 --> 19:28.293
<i>♪ I got my fingers on it</i>

19:28.377 --> 19:30.128
[rock music]

19:30.212 --> 19:31.839
♪♪

20:03.745 --> 20:05.455
I got some business
I got to take care of.

20:05.539 --> 20:06.248
You going out?

20:06.290 --> 20:07.624
Yeah, for a while,

20:07.708 --> 20:09.710
I got to run
an errand for a fellow.

20:09.793 --> 20:11.295
You want to
come along, Henry?

20:11.378 --> 20:14.506
Uh... no.
No, you go ahead.

20:14.590 --> 20:16.008
Okay.

20:16.091 --> 20:17.885
See you later.

20:27.644 --> 20:29.396
Want to play cards?

20:31.064 --> 20:31.940
Mm-hmm.

20:44.828 --> 20:46.914
What was your daddy like?

20:46.997 --> 20:48.582
My daddy?

20:49.791 --> 20:50.626
He used to drive a truck

20:50.709 --> 20:53.045
before he got
his legs cut off.

20:54.963 --> 20:56.924
I remember one time,

20:57.007 --> 21:00.260
he brought me and my
little brother home bicycles.

21:00.344 --> 21:01.678
He had delivered
some that day

21:01.762 --> 21:04.222
and he had
a couple left over.

21:04.306 --> 21:07.184
But, mine was
way too big for me,

21:07.267 --> 21:10.854
and my brother,
he couldn't ride his anyway.

21:10.938 --> 21:12.689
Daddy, he said
I'd grow into it,

21:12.773 --> 21:14.983
but I never did.

21:15.067 --> 21:16.944
Why not?

21:17.027 --> 21:18.445
I never got the chance.

21:18.528 --> 21:20.155
They sold it.

21:20.238 --> 21:21.782
They sold them both.

21:24.159 --> 21:26.244
So you have a brother?

21:27.913 --> 21:30.749
My brother,
he had a bone disorder.

21:30.832 --> 21:34.086
He was a little deformed.

21:34.169 --> 21:35.837
What happened to him?

21:37.130 --> 21:38.715
He died.

21:42.761 --> 21:47.307
I can't ever remember
really liking my daddy.

21:47.391 --> 21:50.018
I wanted to,
I really did.

21:51.561 --> 21:56.024
One time he bought me,
when I was about five,

21:56.108 --> 21:58.276
he bought me
an ice cream cone

21:58.360 --> 22:00.278
and I dropped it.

22:01.071 --> 22:02.030
And he slapped me

22:02.114 --> 22:04.366
and made me
pick it up and eat it.

22:05.742 --> 22:07.744
I never liked my daddy.

22:10.414 --> 22:11.999
One time,

22:12.082 --> 22:14.126
when my momma was at work,

22:14.209 --> 22:16.378
and I was about 13,

22:16.461 --> 22:17.462
he come into my room

22:17.546 --> 22:21.049
and he told me
to take my shirt off

22:21.133 --> 22:24.428
'cause he wanted to see
how I was developed.

22:24.511 --> 22:25.595
And when I wouldn't

22:25.679 --> 22:28.598
he got real mad
and he hit me.

22:28.682 --> 22:30.350
And he told me he had a right

22:30.434 --> 22:32.978
because he was my daddy
and I was his daughter

22:33.061 --> 22:36.523
and he fed me
and let me live in his house

22:36.606 --> 22:39.151
and he could do
whatever he wanted.

22:40.193 --> 22:41.778
And he did.

22:43.780 --> 22:47.534
Then he started coming into
my room a lot after that.

22:48.535 --> 22:49.369
And I didn't fight him

22:49.453 --> 22:51.663
because when I did
he just hit me.

22:52.956 --> 22:55.917
I was afraid I was
going to have a baby

22:56.001 --> 22:58.879
and that my baby
would be deformed,

22:58.962 --> 23:01.465
but I never got pregnant.

23:03.717 --> 23:06.553
I tried to tell Mama,

23:06.636 --> 23:09.097
but she didn't
want to hear about it.

23:10.557 --> 23:11.892
She pretended
not to believe me,

23:11.975 --> 23:14.269
but I knew she did.

23:17.564 --> 23:19.566
It sure is good to talk...

23:19.649 --> 23:22.235
to talk to you, Henry,

23:22.319 --> 23:24.571
because I know
you're not judgmental

23:24.654 --> 23:26.907
or anything like that.

23:29.910 --> 23:31.703
I never would have married
Leroy in the first place

23:31.787 --> 23:34.748
if I hadn't wanted to get
away from Daddy so bad.

23:34.831 --> 23:37.667
Didn't get along
with your daddy, huh?

23:45.008 --> 23:46.927
Did you really
kill your mama?

23:47.010 --> 23:48.261
What?

23:49.221 --> 23:52.599
Did you really
kill your mama?

23:52.682 --> 23:54.810
I guess I did.

23:56.394 --> 23:58.230
How did it happen?

24:00.107 --> 24:02.359
I stabbed her.

24:03.151 --> 24:06.238
Otis said you hit her
with a baseball bat.

24:06.321 --> 24:08.240
Otis said that?

24:08.323 --> 24:09.658
Yeah.

24:09.741 --> 24:11.993
Well, he's mistaken.

24:13.995 --> 24:15.872
Well, don't tell him
I told you,

24:15.956 --> 24:18.208
he made me promise.

24:19.668 --> 24:22.254
She must have
treated you real bad.

24:27.551 --> 24:29.678
She was a whore.

24:30.846 --> 24:33.306
My mama was a whore.

24:35.058 --> 24:37.435
But I don't
fault her for that.

24:37.519 --> 24:40.689
It ain't what she done,
it's how she done it.

24:44.067 --> 24:45.235
As long as I can remember

24:45.318 --> 24:48.530
she'd be bringing men
up to the house.

24:48.613 --> 24:50.031
My daddy was there too,

24:50.115 --> 24:52.784
but it didn't matter
none to her.

24:55.078 --> 24:57.539
She'd make me watch it.

24:58.623 --> 25:00.625
That's creepy.

25:00.709 --> 25:03.670
She beat me, too.
A lot.

25:04.671 --> 25:08.175
She'd beat me when
I wouldn't watch it.

25:08.258 --> 25:11.052
And sometimes she'd beat me,

25:11.136 --> 25:13.680
make me wear a dress

25:13.763 --> 25:16.683
and watch her doing it.

25:16.766 --> 25:19.019
Then they'd laugh at me.

25:19.102 --> 25:21.396
She made you wear a dress?

25:21.479 --> 25:23.607
You think I'm lying?

25:27.861 --> 25:30.155
I feel like I know you.

25:30.238 --> 25:33.617
Like, I've known you
for a long time.

25:33.700 --> 25:36.411
I feel like I've known you
for ever and ever.

25:44.920 --> 25:48.048
Yeah...

25:48.131 --> 25:50.550
I killed my mama.

25:52.052 --> 25:53.470
One night,

25:53.553 --> 25:56.973
It was my 14th birthday

25:57.057 --> 26:01.811
and she was drunk
and we had an argument.

26:02.938 --> 26:05.398
She hit me
with a whiskey bottle.

26:07.609 --> 26:09.694
And I shot her.

26:09.778 --> 26:11.821
I shot her dead.

26:12.822 --> 26:15.450
I thought you said
you stabbed her?

26:20.622 --> 26:22.707
Oh yeah.

26:24.334 --> 26:26.211
That's right.

26:27.545 --> 26:29.798
I stabbed her.

26:33.009 --> 26:35.345
[door opening]

26:39.015 --> 26:40.308
Hey.

26:46.523 --> 26:48.608
Anything good on TV?

26:51.444 --> 26:53.029
[upbeat music]

26:53.113 --> 26:54.698
♪♪

27:49.544 --> 27:51.504
<i>I got a job today.</i>

27:51.588 --> 27:52.839
<i>Oh yeah?
Doing what?</i>

27:52.922 --> 27:54.549
<i>At a beauty parlor.</i>

27:54.632 --> 27:55.425
<i>A beauty parlor?</i>

27:55.508 --> 27:57.093
<i>I'm a shampoo girl.</i>

27:57.177 --> 27:58.303
<i>What's that?</i>

27:58.386 --> 27:59.846
<i>What's it sound like,
you dummy?</i>

27:59.929 --> 28:00.764
<i>How the hell should I know?</i>

28:00.847 --> 28:02.724
<i>You ever seen me
in a beauty parlor?</i>

28:02.807 --> 28:04.184
<i>I give shampoos,</i>

28:04.267 --> 28:05.518
<i>a woman gets her
hair shampooed</i>

28:05.602 --> 28:08.730
<i>before she gets it cut
and I do it.</i>

28:08.813 --> 28:10.523
<i>They pay you for that?</i>

28:10.607 --> 28:11.983
<i>Of course they do.</i>

28:12.067 --> 28:13.151
<i>Besides, I used to
do it some back home</i>

28:13.234 --> 28:14.903
<i>after I met Leroy.</i>

28:14.986 --> 28:17.405
Do you like it better
than dancing naked?

28:17.489 --> 28:18.907
Don't start with me, Otis.

28:18.990 --> 28:20.408
[chuckles]

28:20.492 --> 28:21.618
You used to dance naked?

28:21.701 --> 28:23.411
Sure, all the time
around the house.

28:23.495 --> 28:24.621
Otis.

28:24.704 --> 28:26.247
Best little naked dancer
you ever saw.

28:26.331 --> 28:27.624
You never.

28:27.707 --> 28:29.376
[chuckles]

28:29.459 --> 28:31.836
Were you really a dancer?

28:31.920 --> 28:34.714
I danced some,
in a club,

28:34.798 --> 28:36.925
and I wasn't naked.

28:37.008 --> 28:39.552
I wore a costume.

28:39.636 --> 28:41.596
But I guess it
wasn't very much.

28:41.679 --> 28:42.931
Oh.

28:43.014 --> 28:45.141
When you gonna dance for us?

28:45.225 --> 28:47.936
When the Pope
pees in his hat, Otis.

28:48.019 --> 28:48.937
[laughs]

28:49.020 --> 28:50.730
Ain't she got
a mouth on her?

28:50.814 --> 28:51.815
I better have
something on me

28:51.898 --> 28:53.817
to defend me
from a pig like you.

28:53.900 --> 28:56.236
- [making pig sounds]
- Otis.

28:58.321 --> 29:01.324
Them pretty earrings
you got on, Becky.

29:01.408 --> 29:03.159
Thank you, Henry.

29:03.243 --> 29:06.579
At least there's one
gentleman at this table.

29:06.663 --> 29:09.207
Oh, I'm sorry, honey.
Now don't get mad.

29:09.290 --> 29:12.710
I was just having a little
fun with you, that's all.

29:12.794 --> 29:14.421
Oh, wait,
I got something to show you.

29:14.504 --> 29:16.172
- What?
- Wait.

29:19.676 --> 29:21.094
Ta-da!

29:22.178 --> 29:23.346
Nice.

29:23.430 --> 29:24.764
Real nice.

29:24.848 --> 29:26.015
Put it on.

29:26.099 --> 29:26.933
Right now?

29:27.016 --> 29:28.518
Uh-huh.

29:29.269 --> 29:31.729
Okay,
but turn around first.

29:31.813 --> 29:33.481
Turn around.

29:57.088 --> 29:59.048
Okay, you can look.

30:00.967 --> 30:02.760
What does it say on there?

30:02.844 --> 30:04.554
I love Chicago.

30:05.638 --> 30:07.515
Looks good,
don't it, Otis?

30:07.599 --> 30:09.184
Uh-huh.

30:10.977 --> 30:12.562
[sighs]

30:12.645 --> 30:14.063
Oh hey, honey,

30:14.147 --> 30:16.900
why don't you bring me a beer,
this one's empty.

30:16.983 --> 30:19.402
I ain't your maid.
Get it yourself.

30:19.486 --> 30:22.530
Aw, now come on, honey,
I ain't askin' you

30:22.614 --> 30:24.574
to wash the windows
or nothing,

30:24.657 --> 30:25.575
I just want a beer.

30:25.658 --> 30:28.995
Come on, bring your poor
old brother a beer, will ya?

30:35.043 --> 30:37.420
Don't do that, Otis,
she's your sister!

30:37.504 --> 30:39.214
Okay, I was only
kidding around, Henry.

30:39.297 --> 30:40.632
Tell her you're sorry.

30:40.715 --> 30:42.717
Okay, I'm sorry.

30:42.800 --> 30:44.802
Now, tell her you
won't do it again.

30:44.886 --> 30:45.970
I won't,

30:46.054 --> 30:48.431
I swear, Becky.
I swear, I won't.

30:49.349 --> 30:50.225
Ow!

30:50.308 --> 30:52.143
Shit, Henry!

30:54.646 --> 30:56.814
Serves you right.

30:56.898 --> 30:57.899
Thank you, Henry.

30:57.982 --> 30:59.692
That's alright.

30:59.817 --> 31:02.028
Listen, I'll do the dishes.

31:02.111 --> 31:03.530
I don't mind.

31:03.613 --> 31:05.240
I don't.

31:18.044 --> 31:21.172
Listen, why don't you boys
go out and get a beer.

31:22.131 --> 31:24.717
I'll do these.
I don't mind, honest.

31:32.976 --> 31:35.103
Well, what do you say, Otis?

31:37.522 --> 31:40.108
You want to go grab a beer?

31:48.157 --> 31:50.535
Sure, I don't mind.

31:56.791 --> 31:58.918
I'll just go spruce up.

32:04.632 --> 32:07.635
That was a real
nice supper, Becky.

32:07.719 --> 32:09.512
Thanks.

32:11.431 --> 32:13.182
Have fun.

32:15.184 --> 32:16.978
Yeah.

32:41.169 --> 32:42.962
[rock music]

32:43.046 --> 32:44.756
♪♪

32:52.722 --> 32:54.641
<i>♪ Well, freshen your makeup</i>

32:54.724 --> 32:56.517
<i>♪ And fix your hair</i>

32:56.601 --> 32:59.812
<i>♪ Straighten your stockings,
I'll soon be there</i>

32:59.896 --> 33:03.316
<i>♪ My Chevy's all gassed up
and ready to go</i>

33:03.399 --> 33:06.527
<i>♪ We're probably going
to wind up in Cicero</i>

33:06.611 --> 33:08.655
<i>♪ 'Cuz we're jukin'</i>

33:08.738 --> 33:11.115
<i>♪ Tonight we're going
to have some fun</i>

33:11.199 --> 33:12.867
<i>♪ Some fun, some fun</i>

33:12.950 --> 33:15.370
<i>♪ Honey, lets go jukin'</i>

33:15.453 --> 33:18.414
<i>♪ A little jukin'
never hurt no one</i>

33:20.166 --> 33:21.668
[eerie music]

33:21.751 --> 33:23.711
♪♪

33:27.548 --> 33:28.800
[woman giggling]

33:28.883 --> 33:30.385
Ooh.

33:32.011 --> 33:34.013
Ooh, easy.

33:34.097 --> 33:36.808
Ah... Mmm...

33:36.891 --> 33:38.142
Easy.

33:39.018 --> 33:41.354
[heavy breathing]

33:41.437 --> 33:43.773
Oh, come on, slow down!

33:43.856 --> 33:45.358
Easy, tiger, easy!

33:45.441 --> 33:46.901
Come on,
slow down.

33:46.984 --> 33:49.112
[grunting]

33:49.195 --> 33:50.613
Now, wait a minute!

33:50.697 --> 33:52.198
Hey come on,
I'm not kidding!

33:52.281 --> 33:54.409
[sound of neck breaking]

33:55.743 --> 33:57.078
Susie?

33:57.578 --> 33:59.205
Susie!

33:59.288 --> 34:02.417
Susie--Ah!

34:02.500 --> 34:03.501
[sound of neck breaking]

34:07.797 --> 34:09.882
[dog barking]

34:37.618 --> 34:38.870
Otis!

34:39.996 --> 34:42.081
Come here,
I'll drive.

34:46.543 --> 34:48.670
[car engine starting]

35:02.143 --> 35:03.186
Fuck.

35:03.269 --> 35:05.104
What's gonna happen
when they find those bodies?

35:05.188 --> 35:07.148
- Nothing.
- What do you mean, "nothing"?

35:07.231 --> 35:09.317
Just what I said, Otis.
Nothing.

35:09.400 --> 35:11.778
Nothing's gonna happen
cause nothing happened.

35:11.861 --> 35:14.822
And I don't know nothing
about it, whatever it is.

35:15.948 --> 35:17.492
Do you?

35:18.409 --> 35:20.077
Hey, I don't know nothin'!

35:21.370 --> 35:22.330
Good.

35:22.413 --> 35:24.040
Oh, fuck.

35:38.930 --> 35:40.681
Feelin' better?

35:41.933 --> 35:43.476
Yeah.

35:52.527 --> 35:54.403
You want some fries?

36:26.769 --> 36:30.022
You telling me you never
killed anybody before?

36:30.106 --> 36:32.149
I ain't saying that.

36:32.233 --> 36:34.527
Then you've killed before,
right?

36:34.610 --> 36:37.405
Well, maybe I didn't
have no choice.

36:37.488 --> 36:40.867
You didn't have no
choice here neither.

36:40.950 --> 36:42.702
Did you?

36:45.162 --> 36:47.164
- Huh?
- Did you?

36:48.165 --> 36:50.501
I don't know,

36:50.585 --> 36:53.087
it ain't the same.

36:53.170 --> 36:55.673
It's always the same

36:55.756 --> 36:58.342
and it's always different.

36:58.426 --> 37:00.678
What do you mean?

37:00.761 --> 37:03.806
It's either you or them,
one way or the other.

37:05.224 --> 37:06.893
Ain't that right?

37:08.603 --> 37:09.812
I don't know.

37:09.896 --> 37:12.106
Open your eyes, Otis.

37:12.189 --> 37:14.233
Look at the world.

37:14.317 --> 37:17.236
It's either you or them.

37:18.321 --> 37:20.656
You know what I mean.

37:24.744 --> 37:26.329
Yeah.

37:29.081 --> 37:30.666
Good.

37:32.126 --> 37:33.961
You want a beer?

37:34.045 --> 37:35.212
Okay.

37:35.463 --> 37:36.881
Okay.

37:48.809 --> 37:51.103
[beer can cracks open]

37:58.903 --> 38:01.405
There was only one left.

38:11.874 --> 38:12.667
...He knows
nothing about this

38:12.750 --> 38:14.085
but you can bet
a dollar to a doughnut

38:14.168 --> 38:15.628
that when he finds out,

38:15.711 --> 38:17.672
and he will find out
'cause I'll tell him,

38:17.755 --> 38:18.965
there'll be hell to pay.

38:19.048 --> 38:19.799
Really?

38:19.840 --> 38:20.883
I'll never go
back there again,

38:20.967 --> 38:22.301
I can tell you that.

38:22.385 --> 38:24.595
Not when he's not there,
anyway.

38:24.679 --> 38:27.723
First of all, there ain't two
of them that speaks English.

38:27.807 --> 38:30.351
It's gone down so badly
with the way it's changed,

38:30.434 --> 38:32.019
it breaks my heart.

38:32.103 --> 38:33.938
It's like that all over.

38:34.021 --> 38:35.731
People spit at you.

38:35.815 --> 38:37.566
I wish I was lying.

38:37.650 --> 38:39.944
Yeah, you can't have a regular
good time in the city no more...

38:40.528 --> 38:43.572
[television]
<i> ...Delicate sensibilities.</i>

38:43.656 --> 38:45.950
<i>Now if you really love me,</i>

38:46.033 --> 38:49.870
<i>you should find me
a beautiful well bred girl,</i>

38:49.954 --> 38:51.789
<i>to give me a little polish.</i>

38:55.001 --> 38:58.295
<i>Favor for favor.
Do you remember?</i>

38:58.379 --> 39:00.840
[pounding on the TV set]

39:11.017 --> 39:13.602
[crash]
- Ah, shit!

39:13.978 --> 39:15.813
[electrical buzzing]

39:18.357 --> 39:20.151
Fuck.

39:22.153 --> 39:24.572
[scoffs]
- What did you do that for?

39:26.240 --> 39:29.243
I guess I got carried away.

39:29.326 --> 39:32.872
Well, I guess you did, Otis.

39:32.955 --> 39:36.167
Shit, I got to have a TV.

39:38.711 --> 39:42.256
Well, let's go shopping.

39:43.299 --> 39:45.009
[eerie music]

39:45.092 --> 39:46.886
♪♪

40:07.198 --> 40:09.325
[car doors slam shut]

40:14.580 --> 40:16.624
[garage door opening]

40:29.303 --> 40:32.098
So what can I
do for you gentlemen?

40:32.181 --> 40:33.557
Oh, It's hot in here,
isn't it?

40:33.641 --> 40:35.226
I've got a cold.

40:35.309 --> 40:37.019
We want a TV.

40:37.812 --> 40:39.939
How much you got to spend?

40:40.022 --> 40:41.232
What do you got?

40:41.315 --> 40:43.567
Fifty bucks.

40:43.651 --> 40:46.570
I can let you have the set
over there for 50 bucks.

40:46.654 --> 40:48.531
Well, turn it on.
We want to see if it works.

40:48.614 --> 40:51.117
- What's the matter,
don't you trust me?
- Uh-uh.

40:52.660 --> 40:55.496
Here, plug it in down there.

40:56.205 --> 40:57.623
Here?

40:57.706 --> 40:59.125
Yeah, down there,
real good.

40:59.208 --> 41:01.043
I see you've had some college.

41:01.127 --> 41:02.503
[television static]

41:02.586 --> 41:04.755
Like you can see,
it works real good.

41:04.839 --> 41:06.423
Just takes a while
to warm up.

41:06.507 --> 41:07.800
It's black and white!

41:07.883 --> 41:09.510
Of course it's
black and white.

41:09.593 --> 41:11.053
What do you expect
for fifty bucks?

41:11.137 --> 41:12.721
Fuckin' 3-D, for Christ's sake?

41:12.805 --> 41:14.431
Well, how much is color?

41:14.515 --> 41:15.933
We want color.

41:16.016 --> 41:18.102
You can't get color
for 50 dollars.

41:18.185 --> 41:20.646
That's okay,
let's see what you got.

41:20.729 --> 41:22.273
What have I got?

41:22.356 --> 41:23.482
You want cable ready?

41:23.566 --> 41:24.775
You want remote control?

41:24.859 --> 41:26.360
You want UHF?

41:26.443 --> 41:29.196
You want 13 inch?
You want 19 inch?

41:29.280 --> 41:30.906
I bet you'd
like to have a 19 inch.

41:30.990 --> 41:32.241
Oh yeah.

41:32.324 --> 41:33.242
You want Sony?

41:33.325 --> 41:34.076
You want Zenith?

41:34.118 --> 41:36.078
Do you want a Gold Star?

41:36.162 --> 41:38.247
What can we get for a $150?

41:38.330 --> 41:40.541
I could let you have
this set for $150.

41:40.624 --> 41:42.042
It's worth $300.

41:42.126 --> 41:43.294
But here,
take a look at this.

41:43.377 --> 41:45.963
For an extra $75,

41:46.046 --> 41:48.757
you can take this $600 set.

41:50.634 --> 41:51.594
What's this?

41:51.677 --> 41:52.887
It's a camcorder.

41:52.970 --> 41:53.679
What?

41:53.721 --> 41:56.724
It's a videotape recorder
and camera rolled into one.

41:56.807 --> 41:58.976
You just pop in a cassette
and you're ready to go.

41:59.059 --> 42:00.519
You can make your
own movies with that?

42:00.603 --> 42:02.354
What else would
you do with it?

42:02.438 --> 42:03.898
How much you want for it?

42:03.981 --> 42:06.400
It's worth a grand,
I'd take half.

42:06.483 --> 42:07.484
Five hundred bucks?

42:07.568 --> 42:10.070
Yeah,
half of a grand is $500.

42:10.154 --> 42:12.781
That's a little more than
we were planning to spend.

42:12.865 --> 42:14.992
I think we should
just take the TV.

42:15.075 --> 42:17.453
Okay,
which one do you want?

42:19.622 --> 42:20.706
The $50 one.

42:20.873 --> 42:22.458
The $50 one.

42:22.541 --> 42:23.500
You guys come in here,

42:23.584 --> 42:26.003
I show this,
I show you that,

42:26.086 --> 42:28.547
and you creeps got
a lousy $50 to spend.

42:28.631 --> 42:30.507
You should have
stopped me a long time ago.

42:30.591 --> 42:31.884
Take the $50 set

42:31.967 --> 42:33.844
and get the hell out,
I'm a busy man.

42:33.928 --> 42:37.056
Well, we were really
counting on a color set.

42:37.139 --> 42:39.350
What's the matter,
you got shit in your ears?

42:39.433 --> 42:42.311
The black and white is $50,
take it or leave it!

42:42.394 --> 42:43.854
Sorry we wasted your time.

42:43.938 --> 42:44.647
Come on, Otis.

42:44.688 --> 42:47.942
Don't give me sorry,
you dumb ass!

42:48.025 --> 42:49.068
Did I stutter?

42:49.151 --> 42:50.986
Gimme the $50 and get out!

42:51.070 --> 42:52.655
I'll give you $50!

42:52.738 --> 42:54.531
[screaming]

42:57.701 --> 42:59.620
[screaming]

43:02.623 --> 43:04.541
God damnit!

43:05.084 --> 43:07.211
Help! Help!

43:07.795 --> 43:09.004
No!

43:16.887 --> 43:18.597
[crash]

43:22.059 --> 43:23.727
Otis,

43:23.811 --> 43:25.354
plug it in.

43:29.900 --> 43:31.277
[electricity buzzing]

43:31.360 --> 43:32.361
[rock music]

43:32.444 --> 43:34.029
<i>♪ Oh baby</i>

43:35.197 --> 43:37.324
<i>♪ You're driving me crazy</i>

43:38.867 --> 43:41.203
<i>♪ I said baby...</i>

43:43.080 --> 43:45.457
Oh, get out of here.
You're too ugly anyways.

43:45.916 --> 43:46.917
Wait.

43:47.001 --> 43:49.128
Lurleen, here's
your Uncle Otis.

43:49.211 --> 43:51.547
Hi, Lurl--
Hi, Lurleen. Hi, honey,

43:51.630 --> 43:54.008
Hi, it's Uncle Otis.

43:54.091 --> 43:56.176
Get out of here.
Henry, come dance with me.

43:56.260 --> 43:57.261
Come on,
come on, just dance.

43:57.344 --> 43:58.387
- Go ahead. Dance
<i>- Who? Me?</i>

43:58.470 --> 43:59.722
- Yeah!
- No, no, no.

43:59.805 --> 44:01.682
Come on, Henry.

44:01.765 --> 44:02.725
Come on.

44:02.808 --> 44:04.476
Come on, do it, Henry.

44:04.560 --> 44:06.103
Go ahead, do it.

44:06.186 --> 44:07.354
That's it.

44:07.438 --> 44:09.106
Go like this.

44:09.189 --> 44:10.524
Get down.

44:10.607 --> 44:12.693
"Boogie" as they say here.

44:12.776 --> 44:14.153
Okay.

44:15.362 --> 44:17.239
♪♪

44:23.704 --> 44:25.873
<i>More, more.</i>

44:25.956 --> 44:28.167
<i>Come on, go for it.</i>

44:28.250 --> 44:30.085
<i>- Come on Henry, that's it.</i>
- That's it.

44:30.169 --> 44:31.920
<i>The hands.
Work them hands, Henry.</i>

44:32.004 --> 44:33.839
<i>That's it, that's it.</i>

44:33.922 --> 44:36.675
<i>Whoa!
Low and behold, what a guy.</i>

44:36.759 --> 44:39.762
<i>Come on, come on.
See, look how good it is.</i>

44:39.845 --> 44:42.431
<i>Right there.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.</i>

44:42.514 --> 44:43.766
<i>Oh, come on.
Come on.</i>

44:43.849 --> 44:45.851
<i>- More, more!</i>
- No, I don't want to.

44:45.934 --> 44:47.519
<i>- More!</i>
- No, I'm okay.

44:47.603 --> 44:50.189
<i>- More damnit!</i>
- Go to bed, Otis.

44:50.606 --> 44:53.525
- Come on, get your face in there.
- Get!

44:53.609 --> 44:55.778
- [laughing]
- Turn it off!

44:55.861 --> 44:57.654
Oh, come on.
Come on.

44:58.072 --> 45:00.199
<i>Ooh...</i>

45:04.119 --> 45:05.662
Turn it off!

45:05.746 --> 45:08.082
<i>- I want more,
just a little bit more.</i>
- All right.

45:08.165 --> 45:09.500
<i>Come on. A little--
That's it, that's it.</i>

45:09.583 --> 45:11.126
<i>This is for Lurleen.
Come on.</i>

45:11.210 --> 45:13.837
<i>- All right, that's it.</i>
- Hi, Lurleen.

45:13.921 --> 45:15.506
<i>Come on, Henry.
Say hi.</i>

45:15.589 --> 45:17.049
- No.
<i>- Say hi, Henry.</i>

45:17.132 --> 45:19.093
- No more, Otis.
<i>- Say hi, Henry.</i>

45:19.176 --> 45:21.637
- No more, Otis!
- He doesn't want to.

45:21.720 --> 45:23.472
<i>- Say hi, Becky.</i>
- I said hi.

45:23.555 --> 45:25.891
<i>Come on. Come on.
Come on. More.</i>

45:28.644 --> 45:30.312
[telephone ringing]

45:31.271 --> 45:32.523
Yeah?

45:34.108 --> 45:36.068
Uh-huh.

45:36.151 --> 45:38.987
Look, I'll do the best I can,
but I don't promise--

45:39.071 --> 45:40.656
Fuck him.

45:41.698 --> 45:42.908
Yeah, yeah, good-bye.

45:42.991 --> 45:44.243
Crazy guy.

45:44.326 --> 45:45.369
What?

45:45.452 --> 45:48.163
Some jerk off hasn't
been out of jail six months,

45:48.247 --> 45:49.957
gets drunk,
gets busted up in a fight.

45:50.040 --> 45:51.291
So he goes home
and gets a gun,

45:51.375 --> 45:53.293
comes back later
and shoots the guy.

45:53.377 --> 45:56.046
They find the gun on him.
He claims he was framed.

45:56.130 --> 45:57.714
- What are you going to do?
- [chuckling]

45:57.798 --> 46:00.384
So, everything going okay?

46:00.467 --> 46:01.343
Yeah.

46:01.427 --> 46:04.721
Okay. You still working
at Bob's Gas?

46:04.805 --> 46:05.597
Yes, sir.

46:05.639 --> 46:07.933
Good.
You working everyday?

46:08.016 --> 46:09.601
Two, three days a week.

46:09.685 --> 46:10.686
It's a little slow now.

46:10.769 --> 46:12.688
Well, if it's less than
two days a week, let me know.

46:12.771 --> 46:14.189
We'll see what
we can do for you.

46:14.273 --> 46:16.150
You still living
at 1801 West North?

46:16.233 --> 46:17.484
Yes, sir.

46:17.568 --> 46:18.235
Alright, good.

46:18.277 --> 46:19.987
I got to cut it
short today, Otis.

46:20.070 --> 46:21.530
My kid's scheduled
for oral surgery.

46:21.613 --> 46:22.656
I promised to take him over.

46:22.739 --> 46:23.907
Sure.

46:23.991 --> 46:25.576
Good.
I'll see you next month?

46:26.535 --> 46:27.661
Take it easy.

46:28.537 --> 46:29.997
Bye.

46:33.667 --> 46:35.586
[coach's whistle blowing]

46:50.684 --> 46:51.602
You got it?

46:51.685 --> 46:53.187
Got what?

46:53.270 --> 46:55.772
- You know what.
- [chuckles]

46:58.025 --> 46:59.526
Here you go.

47:00.611 --> 47:02.362
You wanna try it?

47:11.079 --> 47:12.414
Oh!

47:13.248 --> 47:15.918
God damn you,
you son of a bitch!

47:16.001 --> 47:17.753
Fuckin'...!

47:19.755 --> 47:21.632
Damn it!

47:24.426 --> 47:26.011
Mother fucker.

47:26.720 --> 47:28.430
Let me see that.

47:29.890 --> 47:32.059
That little fuckin' bastard.
I ought to kill him.

47:32.142 --> 47:33.810
I ought to cut his
fuckin' head off.

47:33.894 --> 47:35.562
That'd be a mistake.

47:35.646 --> 47:37.314
Look who's talking.

47:38.065 --> 47:40.150
Watch your mouth, Otis.

47:41.568 --> 47:43.487
I'm sorry, Henry.

47:43.570 --> 47:44.905
You kill that high school boy,

47:44.988 --> 47:47.658
they're going to slap your ass
right back in jail, Otis.

47:47.741 --> 47:49.243
That's a promise.

47:49.326 --> 47:52.079
I mean, people have
seen you together.

47:52.162 --> 47:54.039
I'd still like
to kill him, though.

47:54.122 --> 47:55.624
I bet you would.

47:55.707 --> 47:58.126
I'd like to kill somebody.

47:58.210 --> 47:59.962
Say that again.

48:00.712 --> 48:02.756
I'd like to kill somebody.

48:02.839 --> 48:05.300
Let's me and you
go for a ride, Otis.

48:05.717 --> 48:07.427
[eerie music]

48:07.511 --> 48:09.179
♪♪

49:35.390 --> 49:37.976
Here, I want to
show you something.

49:39.936 --> 49:41.104
Where'd you get this?

49:41.188 --> 49:43.565
Careful, Otis,
it's loaded.

49:44.316 --> 49:45.400
Where'd you get it?

49:45.484 --> 49:47.319
Guns are easy to get.

49:47.402 --> 49:49.613
I can make a phone call
and get a gun.

49:49.696 --> 49:51.490
Anybody can get a gun, Otis.

49:51.573 --> 49:53.367
What do you got
in mind, Henry?

49:53.450 --> 49:55.202
What do you think?

49:57.871 --> 49:59.247
I don't know.

50:00.624 --> 50:02.376
Put up the hood.

50:02.459 --> 50:03.335
Why?

50:03.418 --> 50:05.629
Just put up the hood, Otis.

50:50.048 --> 50:51.842
You guys need any help?

50:52.217 --> 50:54.428
Otis, do you need some help,

50:54.511 --> 50:56.638
or can you do it yourself?

50:59.891 --> 51:01.852
[gun shots]

51:05.230 --> 51:07.649
[laughing]

51:09.901 --> 51:11.778
- Feel better?
- Yeah.

51:12.654 --> 51:14.406
Alright.

51:26.960 --> 51:29.296
<i>If you shoot somebody
in the head with a.45</i>

51:29.379 --> 51:31.590
<i>every time you kill somebody</i>

51:31.673 --> 51:34.134
<i>it becomes like
your fingerprint, see?</i>

51:34.217 --> 51:36.261
<i>But if you strangle one
and stab another,</i>

51:36.344 --> 51:39.222
<i>one you cut up,
one you don't,</i>

51:39.306 --> 51:41.349
<i>then the police
don't know what to do.</i>

51:41.433 --> 51:43.977
<i>They think you're
four different people.</i>

51:44.060 --> 51:46.021
<i>What they really like,</i>

51:46.104 --> 51:48.106
<i>what makes their job
so much easier,</i>

51:48.190 --> 51:49.816
<i>is a pattern.</i>

51:49.900 --> 51:52.277
What they call
a modus operandi.

51:53.445 --> 51:54.905
That's Latin.

51:54.988 --> 51:56.907
Bet you didn't know
any Latin, did ya?

51:56.990 --> 51:58.700
Big fuckin' deal.

51:59.868 --> 52:00.827
What?

52:00.911 --> 52:02.621
Nothing.

52:04.539 --> 52:06.541
<i>It's like a trail
of shit, Otis.</i>

52:06.625 --> 52:09.753
<i>It's like a blood droppings
from a deer you've shot</i>

52:09.836 --> 52:12.130
<i>and all they gotta do
is follow those droppings</i>

52:12.214 --> 52:15.634
<i>and pretty soon they're
going to find their deer.</i>

52:21.640 --> 52:24.017
<i>[man screaming]</i>

52:26.061 --> 52:28.355
Why do we use a gun?

52:30.232 --> 52:32.025
You could use a gun.

52:32.108 --> 52:33.693
I'm not saying
you can't use a gun.

52:33.777 --> 52:36.613
Just don't use
the same gun twice.

52:39.115 --> 52:42.244
<i>The most important thing
is to keep moving.</i>

52:42.327 --> 52:45.914
<i>That way they might
never catch up to you.</i>

52:45.997 --> 52:47.040
I'm gonna have to pack up

52:47.123 --> 52:49.125
and be on the move too,
pretty soon.

52:49.209 --> 52:50.919
Where are you going?

52:51.002 --> 52:52.462
Nowhere.

52:52.546 --> 52:54.798
You wanna come?

52:54.881 --> 52:57.133
We could be back this way
in about a month.

52:58.426 --> 53:00.011
I'm not supposed
to leave the state

53:00.095 --> 53:01.012
without telling them.

53:01.096 --> 53:01.972
So who's gonna know?

53:02.055 --> 53:05.225
As long as you show up
when you're supposed to?

53:05.308 --> 53:08.103
What if they check up
on me at work?

53:08.186 --> 53:11.481
Well, no plan is perfect.

53:19.698 --> 53:21.366
[eerie music]

53:21.449 --> 53:22.909
♪♪

54:08.455 --> 54:09.915
<i>- Bring her in.
- No!</i>

54:09.998 --> 54:11.416
<i>Bring her in, Otis.</i>

54:11.499 --> 54:12.834
<i>- No!
- Come on.</i>

54:12.918 --> 54:14.544
<i>That's it.
Yeah, yeah.</i>

54:14.628 --> 54:17.047
<i>Sit down.
Sit her down.</i>

54:17.130 --> 54:18.298
<i>Oh, good, good,
good, good, good.</i>

54:18.381 --> 54:19.674
<i>Get her blouse off.</i>

54:19.758 --> 54:21.426
<i>Take it off.
Take it off.</i>

54:21.509 --> 54:24.179
<i>- Oh yeah, Otis. Good.
- No! No!</i>

54:24.262 --> 54:26.181
<i>- Nice, nice. Yeah, yeah.
- No! No!</i>

54:26.264 --> 54:27.849
<i>Skirt, skirt, skirt.</i>

54:27.933 --> 54:29.684
<i>Do it, Otis!
You're a star!</i>

54:29.768 --> 54:31.728
[laughing]
<i>Oh!</i>

54:33.229 --> 54:35.690
[man gagged and screaming]

54:36.816 --> 54:38.485
[thud]

54:38.568 --> 54:39.653
<i>Shut up!</i>

54:39.736 --> 54:41.446
<i>[thud]
Shut up!</i>

54:42.948 --> 54:45.492
<i>I'll do what the hell
I want to do, bitch!</i>

54:45.575 --> 54:48.161
<i>- Huh? Huh?
- Leave me alone!</i>

54:48.244 --> 54:49.663
<i>- Leave me alone!
- Do it, Otis.</i>

54:49.746 --> 54:51.706
- [laughing]
<i>- Do it.</i>

54:51.790 --> 54:53.416
<i>Henry, look.
Henry, look.</i>

54:53.500 --> 54:55.085
<i>You got it.</i>

54:55.168 --> 54:57.420
<i>- Go for it, boy.
- No! No!</i>

54:57.837 --> 55:00.548
<i>- No! No!
- Wave! Wave!</i>

55:00.632 --> 55:03.009
<i>- Shut up!
- No! No! No!</i>

55:03.093 --> 55:05.303
<i>Get the goddamn kid!</i>

55:07.305 --> 55:09.432
[screaming]

55:11.518 --> 55:14.104
[sound of struggling]

55:28.827 --> 55:29.828
[sound of neck breaking]

55:29.911 --> 55:31.997
- [laughing]
<i>- Son of a bitch!</i>

55:32.080 --> 55:33.623
<i>Henry, look!</i>

55:33.707 --> 55:35.542
[sound of neck breaking]

55:37.293 --> 55:38.878
[grunts]

55:38.962 --> 55:41.256
[panting]

55:45.719 --> 55:48.555
[stabbing and groaning sounds]

56:01.067 --> 56:02.485
<i>Hey, Henry?</i>

56:02.569 --> 56:03.862
<i>Henry?</i>

56:03.945 --> 56:05.780
[laughing]

56:05.864 --> 56:07.115
<i>What?</i>

56:07.198 --> 56:09.909
<i>- Hi! Bye!
- Looky here, where you at.</i>

56:09.993 --> 56:11.494
<i>Say hello, honey!</i>

56:11.578 --> 56:12.746
<i>Say bye.</i>

56:12.829 --> 56:14.205
<i>I have to wave to my buddy.</i>

56:14.289 --> 56:15.373
<i>Henry, hi.</i>

56:15.457 --> 56:17.083
<i>Henry, look at this, Henry.</i>

56:17.167 --> 56:18.793
<i>Ain't it beautiful?</i>

56:20.378 --> 56:21.463
<i>Otis!</i>

56:21.546 --> 56:22.922
<i>No, Otis!</i>

56:23.006 --> 56:24.257
<i>Otis!</i>

56:24.340 --> 56:26.092
<i>No!</i>

56:26.509 --> 56:27.761
<i>Let's go!</i>

56:27.844 --> 56:30.305
[footsteps on video]

56:32.974 --> 56:34.976
<i>I wanted to do that, Henry.</i>

56:40.065 --> 56:42.650
[video tape rewinding]

56:43.610 --> 56:45.028
What are you doing?

56:46.029 --> 56:48.031
I want to see it again.

56:49.741 --> 56:52.535
[tape player clicking]

56:57.749 --> 56:59.459
[eerie music]

56:59.542 --> 57:01.419
♪♪

57:08.093 --> 57:10.428
[woman's screams echoing]

57:14.099 --> 57:16.309
♪♪

57:26.736 --> 57:28.988
In jail?
Are you sure?

57:32.867 --> 57:35.870
Is Lurleen there?
Does she know?

57:37.330 --> 57:38.998
In the what?

57:39.082 --> 57:40.917
In the army?

57:42.710 --> 57:44.587
Go get her, will you?

57:49.342 --> 57:52.053
Hi--
Hi.

57:52.137 --> 57:55.098
Hi, hi.

57:55.181 --> 57:58.059
Do you miss me?

57:58.143 --> 58:00.395
I miss you.

58:04.524 --> 58:07.777
You did?
That's wonderful.

58:09.237 --> 58:11.447
Are you being a good girl?

58:13.533 --> 58:15.618
Uh...

58:15.702 --> 58:17.912
I don't think so, honey.

58:17.996 --> 58:21.332
I know I promised,
but, uh...

58:21.416 --> 58:24.377
a couple of things
have happened here.

58:27.338 --> 58:30.216
I know,
he is a good soldier.

58:33.303 --> 58:36.723
Soon.
Real soon, I promise.

58:39.559 --> 58:42.896
I love you, too.

58:42.979 --> 58:45.899
Yeah, put your
grandma back on, okay?

58:49.068 --> 58:50.820
Hi.

58:53.114 --> 58:56.701
I know.
I'll think about it.

58:59.162 --> 59:01.623
I can't right now.

59:02.916 --> 59:05.043
I will. Soon.

59:06.961 --> 59:08.254
I can't talk anymore, okay?

59:08.338 --> 59:09.714
I gotta go.

59:10.757 --> 59:12.133
Okay.

59:12.217 --> 59:13.676
Bye.

59:20.308 --> 59:21.476
<i>Great, great.</i>

59:21.559 --> 59:23.770
<i>Oh! Oh!</i>

59:24.729 --> 59:26.898
<i>I got one,
I got one, here, look.</i>

59:26.981 --> 59:28.650
<i>Oh, look, look,
look, look, look.</i>

59:28.733 --> 59:29.943
<i>Oh, just look at this,
look at this.</i>

59:30.026 --> 59:31.236
<i>Tight, huh.
There, huh.</i>

59:31.319 --> 59:32.278
<i>Yeah, no, no.</i>

59:32.362 --> 59:33.738
<i>No. Oh, no,
I like this one better.</i>

59:33.821 --> 59:35.782
<i>Look, Henry.
Look, Henry. Henry, look.</i>

59:35.865 --> 59:37.742
<i>Oh, yeah, I love it.
I love her.</i>

59:37.825 --> 59:40.286
<i>Look it how she looks.
Isn't she pretty?</i>

59:40.370 --> 59:41.704
<i>Oh God,
look at that dress.</i>

59:41.788 --> 59:43.498
<i>Look at the way it moves.</i>

59:43.581 --> 59:45.041
Oh yeah!

59:45.124 --> 59:47.126
<i>Pull up next to her,
real slow.</i>

59:47.210 --> 59:48.753
[camera smashes]
Oh!

59:48.836 --> 59:51.547
Look what you did!

59:51.631 --> 59:52.840
Oh God!

59:52.924 --> 59:55.134
Oh Jesus!

59:56.886 --> 59:58.596
Look at it, it's ruined.

59:58.680 --> 01:00:01.099
Damn, Henry, you ought to
look where you're drivin'.

01:00:01.182 --> 01:00:02.600
Who the hell told you
to stick your head

01:00:02.684 --> 01:00:03.810
out the window, anyway?

01:00:03.893 --> 01:00:04.936
You could have killed me!

01:00:05.019 --> 01:00:06.062
Oh, that's right.

01:00:06.145 --> 01:00:07.855
Blame it on me.

01:00:08.523 --> 01:00:10.942
Oh, this fucking camera!

01:00:12.485 --> 01:00:14.821
What did you do that for?

01:00:14.904 --> 01:00:16.781
It wasn't any good anymore.

01:00:16.864 --> 01:00:18.116
Could have fixed it.

01:00:18.199 --> 01:00:20.326
Shit, the lens was
busted right off!

01:00:20.410 --> 01:00:21.953
- Could have fixed it.
- How do you know,

01:00:22.036 --> 01:00:23.997
you a camera repair man?

01:00:25.456 --> 01:00:26.249
You should have
said something.

01:00:26.291 --> 01:00:28.042
You didn't give me
a chance, Otis.

01:00:28.126 --> 01:00:29.961
You threw the fucker
right out the window.

01:00:30.044 --> 01:00:31.379
It ain't my fault it broke.

01:00:31.462 --> 01:00:33.172
Oh right.

01:00:35.550 --> 01:00:37.051
Go back and get it,
if you want.

01:00:37.135 --> 01:00:38.720
Yeah.

01:00:46.227 --> 01:00:47.353
Want to get a beer?

01:00:47.437 --> 01:00:49.564
Not particularly.

01:00:49.647 --> 01:00:50.857
I want a beer.

01:00:50.940 --> 01:00:52.567
[tires screech]

01:00:53.359 --> 01:00:55.528
If you want
a beer so bad, Otis,

01:00:55.611 --> 01:00:58.406
go ahead and get one.

01:00:58.489 --> 01:01:00.366
All right, I will.

01:01:04.704 --> 01:01:06.581
- See you later?
- Yeah.

01:01:12.795 --> 01:01:14.547
I talked to Lurleen.

01:01:15.590 --> 01:01:16.924
Yeah?

01:01:17.675 --> 01:01:19.177
You'd like her.

01:01:20.219 --> 01:01:22.055
God, I miss her.

01:01:23.264 --> 01:01:24.932
I'm thinking...

01:01:25.016 --> 01:01:27.435
I might be
heading on back home.

01:01:28.770 --> 01:01:30.271
I quit.

01:01:30.355 --> 01:01:31.564
You quit what?

01:01:33.691 --> 01:01:35.318
My job.

01:01:35.485 --> 01:01:36.694
What happened?

01:01:36.778 --> 01:01:37.779
Nothing.

01:01:37.862 --> 01:01:40.406
I just figured
it was time to go home.

01:01:43.659 --> 01:01:45.286
You want to come with me?

01:01:47.038 --> 01:01:49.248
I thought you wanted
to make some money?

01:01:49.332 --> 01:01:52.085
Yeah, but,

01:01:52.168 --> 01:01:53.294
I'm thinking,

01:01:53.378 --> 01:01:56.089
I don't want to bring
Lurleen up here after all.

01:01:56.172 --> 01:01:58.049
You know,
that was my intention.

01:01:59.634 --> 01:02:03.346
[sighs]
There's just too much
going on up here.

01:02:03.429 --> 01:02:05.306
She'd get lost.

01:02:07.892 --> 01:02:10.478
We're better off
living with Mama.

01:02:12.605 --> 01:02:14.774
I can work back home.

01:02:14.857 --> 01:02:17.527
I won't make as much money,
I'm sure, but

01:02:17.610 --> 01:02:19.737
we won't need as much either.

01:02:19.821 --> 01:02:21.864
I like living with Mama.

01:02:24.325 --> 01:02:26.244
You could stay there, too.

01:02:28.704 --> 01:02:30.873
You figure it's
safe to go back?

01:02:30.957 --> 01:02:32.667
I hope so.

01:02:33.668 --> 01:02:35.169
Leroy's in jail for murder

01:02:35.253 --> 01:02:38.005
and his bond's
a million dollars.

01:02:38.089 --> 01:02:40.466
So unless he wins the lottery,

01:02:40.550 --> 01:02:43.803
Leroy won't be going anywhere
for quite a while.

01:02:45.221 --> 01:02:46.889
Where's Otis?

01:02:47.640 --> 01:02:51.227
He had a dinner date,
I think he said.

01:02:51.310 --> 01:02:52.937
Really?

01:02:53.020 --> 01:02:54.313
Well.

01:02:56.357 --> 01:02:58.025
Come with me?

01:02:58.776 --> 01:03:00.486
